oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Crop health, quality, protection
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This work, which is part of a project called Biocomes (www.biocomes.eu), is financially supported by the European Union and it focuses on the control of the cabbage moth Mamestra brassicae (Linnaeus, 1758) (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae) through mass release of the egg parasitoid Telenomus sp. (Hymenoptera: Scelionidae).
